    <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true">IMPORTANT - </text><text styleclass="Body Text" style="font-weight:bold; font-style:italic;" translate="true">MechDesigner</text><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Body Text" style="text-decoration:underline;" translate="true">automatically</text><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true"> saves and opens all of the Motion tabs when you save and open a </text><text styleclass="Body Text" style="font-weight:bold; font-style:italic; text-decoration:underline;" translate="true">MechDesigner</text><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true"> file. </text></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="Body Text" style="text-decoration:none;" translate="true">Thus, when working in the normal way, it is not necessary to save the </text><text styleclass="Body Text" style="font-weight:bold; font-style:italic; text-decoration:none;" translate="true">MotionDesigner</text><text styleclass="Body Text" style="text-decoration:none;" translate="true"> motion files. </text></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true">However, you can save and open motions with the File toolbar</text></para>
